<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
<taxonomicName authority="Holdhaus, 1904" authorityName="Holdhaus" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Microlestes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microlestes luctuosus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luctuosus">Microlestes luctuosus (Holdhaus, 1904)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
Southern Europe and Southwest Asia, widespread and common in Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Arndt, E." journalOrPublisher="Pensoft, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Ground Beetles (Carabidae) of Greece." year="2011">Arndt et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1082">
It prefers warm, dry places (
<bibRefCitation author="Cardenas Talaveron, A." journalOrPublisher="Mediterranea Serie de Estudios Biologicos" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="147 - 163" title="Fenologia de las Espacies de Carabidos (ColeopteraCarabidae) Mas Abundantes en la Cuenca de Bembezar (NW. de la Provincia de Cordoba)" volume="8" year="1985">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Cárdenas">Cardenas</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Talaverón">Talaveron</normalizedToken>
and Piella 1985
</bibRefCitation>
) on clayey soils (
<bibRefCitation author="Trautner, J." journalOrPublisher="Josef Margraf, Aichtal" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" title="Tiger Beetles Ground Beetles. Illustrated Key to the Cicindelidae and Carabidae of Europe." year="1987">Trautner and Geigenmüller 1987</bibRefCitation>
). It may be found in areas of tall vegetation, those of over 20 cm in height (
<bibRefCitation author="Fadda, S." journalOrPublisher="Comptes Rendus Biologies" pageId="0" pageNumber="1082" pagination="532 - 546" title="Consequences of the Cessation of 3000 Years of Grazing on Dry Mediterranean Grassland Ground-Active Beetle Assemblages." volume="331" year="2008">Fadda et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). In this study it was found in the cotton field in the heterogeneous area (n = 2), the cotton field in the homogeneous area (n = 1), the olive grove in the heterogeneous area (n = 57), the olive grove in the homogeneous area (n = 6), the wheat field in the heterogeneous area (n = 649) and the wheat field in the homogeneous area (n = 142).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
